        {"id": 142, "answer": "B", "questions": {"original": "An engineering student has to secure 36% marks to pass. He gets 130 marks and fails by 14 marks. The maximum number of marks obtained by him is?"}, "options": [{"label": "A", "text": "881"}, {"label": "B", "text": "400"}, {"label": "C", "text": "778"}, {"label": "D", "text": "566"}, {"label": "E", "text": "281"}], "explanation": "130\n14\n-------\n361------ 144\n100%------? => 400\nAnswer: B", "components": "* First Clause\n** Subject: An engineering student\n** Verb: has to secure\n** Object: 36% marks\n** Complement: to pass\n* Second Clause\n** Subject: He\n** Verb: gets\n** Object: 130 marks\n* Third Clause\n** Subject: He\n** Verb: fails\n** Complement: by 14 marks\n* Fourth Clause (Question)\n** Subject: The maximum number of marks\n** Verb: is\n** Complement: obtained by him"},
        {"id": 185, "answer": "C", "questions": {"original": "A single refined oil can contains 20% impurities. After double\u2013refining, it contains 4% impurities. How much of double-refined oil can be obtained from 30 litres of single refined oil?"}, "options": [{"label": "A", "text": "24.0 litres"}, {"label": "B", "text": "24.8 litres"}, {"label": "C", "text": "25.0 litres"}, {"label": "D", "text": "25.5 litres"}, {"label": "E", "text": "26.5 litres"}], "explanation": "On double-refining impurity decreases from 20% to 4%, but the amount of pure oil in both cases remains constant,\ni.e, 96% of double refined oil = 80% of single refined oil.\nLet x be the quantity of double-refined oil\nThen 96*x/100 = 80*30/100, x = 30*80 /96 = 25\nANSWER:C", "components": "* First Clause\n** Subject: A single refined oil can\n** Verb: contains\n** Object: 20% impurities\n* Second Clause\n** Subject: it\n** Verb: contains\n** Object: 4% impurities\n** Complement: After double-refining\n* Third Clause (Question)\n** Subject: How much of double-refined oil\n** Verb: can be obtained\n** Complement: from 30 litres of single refined oil"},
        {"id": 67, "answer": "A", "questions": {"original": "Proportion of Yuvaraj\u2019s age to Ganguly\u2019s age is 4:3. Yuvaraj will be 26 years old after 6 years. What is the age of Ganguly now?"}, "options": [{"label": "A", "text": "15 years"}, {"label": "B", "text": "16 years"}, {"label": "C", "text": "19 years"}, {"label": "D", "text": "22 years"}, {"label": "E", "text": "25 years"}], "explanation": "Current ages of Yuvaraj = 4A and\nGanguly = 3A\nSo that 4A + 6 = 26\nA = 5\nCurrent age of Ganguly = 3(A)\n=> 3 x 5 =15 years", "components": "* First Clause\n** Subject: Proportion of Yuvaraj’s age to Ganguly’s age\n** Verb: is\n** Complement: 4:3\n* Second Clause\n** Subject: Yuvaraj\n** Verb: will be\n** Complement: 26 years old\n** Additional phrase: after 6 years\n* Third Clause (Question)\n** Subject: What (referring to the age of Ganguly)\n** Verb: is\n** Complement: the age of Ganguly now"},
        {"id": 99, "answer": "D", "questions": {"original": "A college has 10 basketball players. A 5-member team and a captain will be selected out of these 10 players. How many different selections can be made?"}, "options": [{"label": "A", "text": "1360"}, {"label": "B", "text": "1380"}, {"label": "C", "text": "1280"}, {"label": "D", "text": "1260"}, {"label": "E", "text": "1460"}], "explanation": "A team of 6 members has to be selected from the 10 players. This can be done in 10C v 6 or 210 ways.\nNow, the captain can be selected from these 6 players in 6 ways.\nTherefore, total ways the selection can be made is 210\u00d76= 1260\nANSWER:D", "components": "* First Clause\n** Subject: A college\n** Verb: has\n** Object: 10 basketball players\n* Second Clause\n** Subject: A 5-member team and a captain\n** Verb: will be selected\n** Complement: out of these 10 players\n* Third Clause (Question)\n** Subject: How many different selections\n** Verb: can be made"},
