        {"id": 952, "answer": "360", "questions": {"original": "Vince can staple 30 reports every 15 minutes.  If he was stapling reports from 8:00 AM until 11:00 PM, how many reports did he staple altogether?"}, "explanation": "In one hour, there are 60 / 15 = <<60/15=4>>4 (15 minutes).\nFrom 8am - 11am, there are 11 - 8 = <<11-8=3>>3 hours.\nIn 3 hours, there are 3 x 4 = <<3*4=12>>12 (15 minutes).\nIn those 3 hours, Vince stapled 12 x 30 = <<12*30=360>>360 reports.", "components": "* First Clause\n** Subject: Vince\n** Verb: can staple\n** Object: 30 reports\n** Complement: every 15 minutes\n* Second Clause (Conditional Clause)\n** Subject: he\n** Verb: was stapling\n** Object: reports\n** Complement: from 8:00 AM until 11:00 PM\n* Third Clause (Question)\n** Subject: he\n** Verb: did staple\n** Object: how many reports\n** Complement: altogether"},
